Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da yin amfani da tallace-tallace masu tayar da hankali
Kwana bakwai bayan da jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa a shafi na hudu a jaridar U.S. daily, mai yaba wa amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada propaganda.
A ranar Laraba, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana game da wani karamin tallafi na China Daily a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa, bayan ya zargi kasar Sin da tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, abin da kasar Sin ta musanta.
zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna, kamar yadda jami'an Amurka suka fada wa kamfanin dillancin labarai na Reuters, wani sabon mataki a yakin neman zaben Washington na matsa lamba a kasar Sin.
Kuma yayin da gwamnatocin kasashen waje suke tallata tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin faɗacewar yakin cinikayya inda juna ke kara harajin shigo da kaya.
A matsayin abin da zai iya hana hakan, a baya, harajin da kasar Sin ta yi a wannan yakin cinikayya, an yi amfani da shi ne wajen kai wa masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohi kamar Iowa, wadda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, in ji masana na kasar Sin da na Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon magajin jihar Iowa, wadda ita ce babbar mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni lahani.
"Kasar Sin, in ji Branstad a wata sanarwa da aka wallafa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register na Lahadi, yanzu tana ninka wannan tashin hankali ta hanyar wallafa tallace-tallace a cikin jaridarmu ta 'yanci".
"Gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da al'adun 'yancin magana da kuma' yancin' yan jarida na Amirka ta wajen yin tallan da ake biya a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A akasin haka, a tashar da ke kan titi a birnin Beijing, za ku ga wasu ra'ayoyi dabam-dabam da ba za ku iya ganin wani abu da zai nuna cewa mutane a kasar Sin suna da ra'ayi dabam-dabam game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba, tun da yake kafofin watsa labarai na kasar Sin suna karkashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
